npredictable in the years ahead.</p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Day-to-day p=
rice swings should get smaller because AI can analyze information much fast=
er and more accurately than humans. It won=E2=80=99t get emotional or overr=
eact to headlines the way people do, and it will constantly fix small prici=
ng mistakes as they happen.</p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">When there <em>is=
</em> a big panic-driven selloff, AI-driven money should step in quicker an=
d more rationally, which could lead to faster recoveries instead of long, d=
rawn-out crashes. This is one of the things I love doing..... sigh the AI c=
ould even front run me. </p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Individual stocks mi=
ght also start moving more on their own fundamentals rather than just risin=
g and falling with the overall market. That=E2=80=99s because personalized =
AI portfolios could gradually replace the big wave of money that currently =
flows in and out of broad index funds and ETFs.</p><p style=3D"margin:10px =
0">For people like me who actually enjoy buying when things look scary (the=
 =E2=80=9Crunning into burning buildings=E2=80=9D trades), I probably won=
=E2=80=99t be as alone anymore. AI systems will likely spot a lot of the sa=
me opportunities I do. They=E2=80=99ll also get better at seeing where thin=
gs are headed, similar to how we use our own price prediction models.</p><p=
 style=3D"margin:10px 0">Interesting times ahead either way.</p><p style=3D=
"margin:10px 0">h.t Cern for the image above. </p><p></p></div></td></tr>
